it doesn’t make any sense, you know.

24:48.250 --> 24:49.958
Because of how I feel.

24:50.958 --> 24:51.958
I...

24:53.167 --> 24:56.292
I wonder all the time
if you think about me.

24:58.167 --> 24:59.167
Zoe.

25:01.209 --> 25:02.250
It’s…

25:03.625 --> 25:05.042
It’s not like that.

25:05.125 --> 25:06.625
I just thought…

25:08.791 --> 25:11.042
you might feel it too.

25:16.042 --> 25:17.666
I have to show you something.

25:31.417 --> 25:33.000
Why are you bringing me home?

25:33.083 --> 25:35.167
I want to talk to you about something.

25:39.083 --> 25:41.125
You have keys to my apartment?

25:41.209 --> 25:42.666
I have a set, yeah.

25:45.167 --> 25:47.791
- What is this, Cole?
- Come on. Just come…

25:49.250 --> 25:51.791
Just come sit down. I-I want to explain.

25:55.083 --> 25:56.541
Have a seat.

25:58.917 --> 26:00.459
You trust me, don’t you?

26:01.167 --> 26:02.541
- Yes.
- Okay.

26:02.625 --> 26:05.125
Have you ever done a search
for yourself online?

26:07.042 --> 26:09.209
Yes. When I was younger.

26:09.292 --> 26:11.250
But not in the last few months, no?

26:12.042 --> 26:14.083
No. Why?

26:14.167 --> 26:17.167
You might be surprised to find out
there’s not very much there.

26:18.292 --> 26:21.292
Nothing about being
accepted early to college or, um...

26:21.375 --> 26:25.708
No press release about you being hired
to run the Machine division at the lab.

26:25.791 --> 26:28.334
Nothing about who you are.

26:31.459 --> 26:33.375
Why do you have keys to my apartment?

26:33.459 --> 26:36.083
The apartment belongs to the lab.

26:36.167 --> 26:37.958
I rented it only a few months ago.

26:41.167 --> 26:42.541
What are you talking about?

26:42.625 --> 26:45.292
Do you ever wonder
why there’s no food in your fridge?

26:45.375 --> 26:47.708
Why everything in here is so new?

26:50.000 --> 26:52.125
This isn’t gonna be easy to say,
and, um…

26:53.167 --> 26:54.334
it’s gonna sound a bit crazy,

26:54.417 --> 26:57.958
but you don’t oversee
the Synthetics division at the lab.

27:01.334 --> 27:02.750
You’re a creation of it.

27:05.167 --> 27:07.000
The reason you scored zero with me

27:07.083 --> 27:10.167
was because the Machine
could see that you were synthetic.

27:11.292 --> 27:13.250
Why would you say this to me?

27:13.334 --> 27:15.042
It was a test.

27:15.125 --> 27:19.250
To see how people would connect with you,
if they would connect with you.

27:19.334 --> 27:23.167
To see how Ash would react to you.
To see if anyone would be able to tell.

27:24.459 --> 27:25.917
Go and look in the mirror.

27:26.000 --> 27:28.500
Look at your eyes really close,
and you’ll see.

27:30.000 --> 27:31.500
You’ll see.

27:34.083 --> 27:36.417
You’ve only been online
for a couple of months.

27:39.708 --> 27:42.209
- Oh, my God.
- I’m so sorry, Zoe.

27:45.250 --> 27:46.750
I should have told you sooner.

27:53.459 --> 27:54.500
Zoe.

27:58.791 --> 27:59.791
Zoe.

28:19.708 --> 28:21.917
To tell you the truth,
I’m a little jealous.

28:22.000 --> 28:24.708
- Why?
- You got to be human.

28:26.125 --> 28:28.625
- But it was a lie.
- Not to me.

28:31.708 --> 28:34.500
You know,
I read that you know when you’re in love

28:34.583 --> 28:37.500
because you can’t fall asleep.

28:37.583 --> 28:40.042
Because your reality
is better than your dreams.

28:40.125 --> 28:42.125
Sounds like Freud.

28:42.209 --> 28:44.500
Eh. Dr. Seuss.

28:49.083 --> 28:50.083
Zoe.

29:03.625 --> 29:05.250
It was a mistake.

29:06.292 --> 29:08.292
I should have told you so much sooner.

29:09.750 --> 29:12.375
I had no idea you would evolve like this.
I didn’t.

29:13.666 --> 29:15.708
Was I designed to have feelings for you?

29:16.459 --> 29:17.833
No.

29:17.917 --> 29:20.666
No. You have tendencies,
just like people, that’s all.

29:23.708 --> 29:26.292
Are you going to deactivate me now?

29:26.375 --> 29:29.000
No. That’s not what you want, is it?

29:31.500 --> 29:33.125
I mean, you know…

29:34.583 --> 29:36.083
this is my life.

29:40.083 --> 29:43.042
I realized I’ve never done anything real.

29:44.958 --> 29:47.541
I’ve never stayed up late
with girlfriends.

29:48.833 --> 29:52.875
I’ve never… talked on a
phone with a boy.

29:56.000 --> 29:57.791
I’ve never worn perfume.

30:00.708 --> 30:03.125
I’d like to show you
some of the things you’ve done.

30:04.750 --> 30:06.292
Okay?

30:17.000 --> 30:18.791
I started here when I was 15.

30:19.833 --> 30:22.375
I was overweight, terrified.

30:24.042 --> 30:26.541
But it’s like
all the memories you gave to Ash.

30:29.375 --> 30:30.791
It didn’t happen.

30:32.000 --> 30:33.583
They happened.

30:33.666 --> 30:35.417
You had real emotional experiences.

30:35.500 --> 30:39.833
How you store those memories or how you
remember them doesn’t make them less real.

30:41.583 --> 30:44.292
- What else happened here?
- Mmm.

30:44.375 --> 30:45.791
- Daydream.
- Mm-hmm.

30:45.875 --> 30:47.541
Study on nice days.

30:48.125 --> 30:51.167
I wrote a whole paper once
on my laptop under that tree.

30:51.250 --> 30:52.500
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

30:52.583 --> 30:54.167
I would sit there

30:54.917 --> 30:56.167
and wonder…

30:57.417 --> 30:59.541
how it was going to turn out for me.

31:01.167 --> 31:03.666
Imagining all the possibilities
of what I could be.

31:05.791 --> 31:11.875
I hated school because I always felt
that I was one among many.

31:11.958 --> 31:14.625
I can understand that feeling
of feeling alone with lots of people.

31:14.708 --> 31:15.541
Yeah.

31:15.625 --> 31:18.018
Some people peak there.
They’re the coolest people at school.

31:18.042 --> 31:20.500
Then the rest of their lives
are very mundane and ordinary.

31:20.583 --> 31:21.583
Like a misfit.

31:21.666 --> 31:22.958
Nerd.

31:23.042 --> 31:24.917
- I felt like that too.
- Nerd, is it?

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
- No. I said I felt like that too.
- Yeah.

31:27.083 --> 31:29.708
- I didn’t think you were a nerd.
- No, I was just...

31:29.791 --> 31:32.750
Nerd! That would be a bit cruel.

31:32.833 --> 31:34.459
“I felt like a misfit.” “Nerd!”

31:34.541 --> 31:36.459
“No, I’m not a nerd. A misfit.”

31:38.541 --> 31:40.541
Miss, I have a question.

31:40.625 --> 31:43.875
What are... What body functions
are we gonna learn today?

31:43.958 --> 31:46.083
This little thing.

31:47.625 --> 31:49.083
It’s a little camel toe.

31:51.541 --> 31:53.833
I don’t think that’s
gonna reproduce anything, really.

31:53.917 --> 31:57.791
Spermatozoid will go in the camel toe.

32:00.541 --> 32:02.209
- It goes in it.
- Go on.

32:02.292 --> 32:05.459
Creates another human being.

32:05.541 --> 32:06.625
Very easy.

32:06.708 --> 32:08.875
That’s the story of humanity.

32:08.958 --> 32:11.278
You’ve been so thorough,
I don’t have any questions at all.

32:11.334 --> 32:13.750
You’ve covered all bases, I think.

32:14.292 --> 32:16.143
- You’re not supposed to be here.
- Oh, sorry.

32:16.167 --> 32:17.750
- Sorry.
- Yeah. Sorry. Right.

32:18.666 --> 32:20.417
Right.

32:37.500 --> 32:39.459
It’s a private research library.

32:39.541 --> 32:41.958
It’s not even open to the grad students.

32:42.042 --> 32:43.250
- It’s nice.
- Yeah.

32:43.334 --> 32:44.875
- It’s got a good smell to it.
- Yeah.

32:44.958 --> 32:47.250
- Smells like old.
- It does have a very old...

32:47.334 --> 32:49.292
- Like an old grandma.
- Like an old grandma?

32:49.375 --> 32:50.583
That’s right.

32:52.708 --> 32:55.292
What was she like,
the person whose memories I have?

32:56.500 --> 32:59.125
Well, it wasn’t just one person.
It was several.

32:59.209 --> 33:01.000
They were mainly students.

33:01.083 --> 33:04.209
And is there anything
from your past inside me?

33:05.375 --> 33:07.459
Anything from what happened with Emma?

33:08.666 --> 33:09.666
No.

33:11.000 --> 33:13.209
The idea was for you to be completely you.

33:14.417 --> 33:17.500
To have your own thoughts and hopes,
flaws.

33:18.708 --> 33:22.083
- I don’t have any flaws.
- No, of course. You don’t have any flaws.

33:22.167 --> 33:24.459
Well, hopes and thoughts anyway.

33:26.541 --> 33:28.625
You never answered my question.

33:29.791 --> 33:33.125
About whether you ever think of me.

33:36.375 --> 33:38.042
Well, of course I have.

33:40.083 --> 33:43.625
But I can’t unsee some of the ways
I’ve seen you, in the beginning.

33:44.791 --> 33:49.083
In some ways, I think it makes me
even more in awe of who you are now.

33:53.958 --> 33:55.375
Yeah.

33:56.125 --> 33:57.334
Everyone walks by here.

34:00.125 --> 34:01.625
I used to watch them all the time.

34:02.583 --> 34:03.583
Hmm.

34:04.625 --> 34:07.459
Coming and going and, you know, waiting…

34:08.791 --> 34:10.625
for the person they loved.

34:13.875 --> 34:15.458
But none of it was real.

34:18.958 --> 34:20.791
I never saw those people.

34:21.666 --> 34:23.791
I was never even here.

34:26.292 --> 34:28.541
Who’s going to love someone
who’s not real?

34:30.125 --> 34:31.750
Zoe, you can’t think like that.

34:40.000 --> 34:42.250
What’s happening to me?

34:48.583 --> 34:50.583
Why are there no tears in my eyes?

34:50.666 --> 34:52.541
Th-There won’t be any tears.

34:54.791 --> 34:57.125
When you were designed,
we couldn’t have imagined

34:57.209 --> 35:00.334
how your emotional life would grow
with these highs and lows.

35:01.083 --> 35:02.875
We didn’t see that coming.

35:02.958 --> 35:07.417
The reason you can’t produce any tears
is your body literally can’t make them.

35:08.375 --> 35:10.917
And I know that’s not fair. I’m sorry.

35:12.292 --> 35:13.666
I’m sorry.

35:56.833 --> 35:59.042
Anyway, I’m gonna go upstairs now.

36:01.541 --> 36:04.000
Anyway, I’m gonna head off. Bye.

36:05.334 --> 36:06.708
- Hey.
- Hey.

36:08.417 --> 36:10.708
- Where did you guys go?
- We just talked.

36:11.750 --> 36:15.334
You know, I read that dating in the office
is a sure path to heartbreak.

36:16.750 --> 36:18.250
You guys gonna be a couple?

36:20.541 --> 36:22.125
I don’t know.

36:23.625 --> 36:24.625
Yeah.

36:35.583 --> 36:38.417
Want to see the future?
You can find it in our pavilion.

36:39.083 --> 36:41.334
Want to see the future?
You can find it in our pavilion.

36:41.417 --> 36:44.083
Another one like there,
which is the opposite of that one.

36:44.167 --> 36:47.000
They didn’t even tell me about this.

36:50.875 --> 36:52.917
She’s just captivating, isn’t she?

36:53.000 --> 36:56.417
- These people have no idea.
- Yeah. They don’t know.

36:59.791 --> 37:03.125
Like the Tin Man over there?
Like, that’s what people are expecting.

37:03.209 --> 37:05.750
- No. That’s right, yeah.
- They have no idea.

37:05.833 --> 37:07.459
Where’s Ash? When’s he on?

37:07.541 --> 37:09.583
- What time is it?
- It’s 9:45.

37:09.666 --> 37:11.346
Probably getting ready for his big speech.

37:11.375 --> 37:13.583
- You think he’s rehearsing the speech?
- I bet he is.

37:13.666 --> 37:15.167
Is he nervous?

37:16.541 --> 37:18.958
Want to see the future?
You can find it in our pavilion.

37:19.042 --> 37:20.791
Accelerated breakthrough…

37:22.167 --> 37:25.209
Want to see the future?
You can find it in our pavilion.

37:26.666 --> 37:30.167
How many of you have considered
the actual possibility

37:30.250 --> 37:32.875
of a relationship with a synthetic?

37:34.209 --> 37:36.209
Of course you haven’t.

37:36.292 --> 37:41.541
Because they are your dog walkers
or maybe a gardener, maybe a housekeeper.

37:42.125 --> 37:44.791
Because they’re primitive, right?
They’re robotic.

37:45.417 --> 37:46.917
They’re not real.

37:48.292 --> 37:49.791
But what if they weren’t?

37:50.875 --> 37:52.042
What if I told you…

37:53.750 --> 37:55.750
I am a synthetic?

37:59.125 --> 38:02.000
What if I told you I could improvise
when I play piano?

38:02.583 --> 38:05.708
That I feel pain? That I can make jokes?

38:05.791 --> 38:08.417
That I can gauge your emotions
and sense what you’re feeling

38:08.500 --> 38:10.583
better than anyone in this room?

38:12.042 --> 38:14.000
Right now, I’m feeling curiosity. Maybe.

38:19.917 --> 38:21.583
I’ll never break your heart.

38:22.583 --> 38:23.708
I’ll never leave you.

38:25.750 --> 38:28.666
And I am designed to love you
and understand you

38:28.750 --> 38:30.875
in ways that humans simply can’t.

38:31.708 --> 38:33.708
And if you want more proof…

38:35.250 --> 38:36.917
just look into my eyes.

38:48.958 --> 38:53.125
The symposium on advancement
in nanosurgery begins in 15 minutes.

39:39.000 --> 39:41.125
This is all interactive.

39:41.209 --> 39:43.666
Translates our voices into images.

39:43.750 --> 39:46.000
It can even hear you whisper.

39:47.042 --> 39:49.334
Whisper.

39:49.958 --> 39:51.583
Whisper. Oh, yeah.

39:52.417 --> 39:53.833
Say something.

39:54.917 --> 39:56.541
Hello. Hi.

39:57.625 --> 39:58.459
Louder.

39:58.541 --> 39:59.791
Hello!

40:00.334 --> 40:01.750
Oh, wow, look.

40:01.833 --> 40:03.167
Hello!

40:03.250 --> 40:05.750
I’m here in an empty room!

40:05.833 --> 40:08.958
Shouting! I feel a little silly!

40:18.459 --> 40:21.250
Whoo!

40:34.791 --> 40:37.083
Fuck!

41:44.750 --> 41:46.500
- Zoe.
- Yeah?

41:49.000 --> 41:52.875
Would you be upset
if we waited… a little bit?

41:54.917 --> 41:56.958
- Do you want me to go?
- No.

41:58.917 --> 42:00.791
I want you to stay.

42:54.375 --> 42:55.459
Exercise.

43:10.708 --> 43:13.292
Incoming.

43:16.917 --> 43:18.500
- Do you like him?
- Yeah.

43:18.583 --> 43:20.292
Why don’t you pull my finger?

43:25.583 --> 43:27.417
So you have many rocks?

43:28.000 --> 43:30.583
Yeah.

43:30.666 --> 43:32.292
- Do you think I’m nice?
- Yeah.

43:32.375 --> 43:33.500
- Really?
- Yeah.

43:33.583 --> 43:36.292
Well, you have to stay here with him.
I’m going home.

43:39.708 --> 43:42.875
- Do you guys wanna stay for dinner?
- No, we’ve, um...

43:42.958 --> 43:44.708
We should get back.

43:44.791 --> 43:46.875
- Caleb really likes her.
- Yeah.

43:48.292 --> 43:51.375
I didn’t mention to him about her,
like what… who she is.

43:51.459 --> 43:56.042
Well, there’s a difference between
what we see and what we know.

43:57.625 --> 44:01.666
So should I tell him or not tell him?
What does that mean?

44:01.750 --> 44:02.791
Tell him.

44:02.875 --> 44:05.958
Tell him.
I’m worried he’s gonna freak out though.

44:06.042 --> 44:07.541
- He likes her, you know.
- Yeah.

44:07.625 --> 44:09.334
- I don’t think so.
- Okay.

44:09.417 --> 44:10.809
- I’ll tell him.
- See you Thursday.

44:10.833 --> 44:13.167
Yeah, thanks.
This was really nice, thank you.

44:13.250 --> 44:15.226
- And bring her.
- Okay, I’ll bring her on Thursday.

44:15.250 --> 44:16.250
Yeah.

44:50.000 --> 44:51.875
Yeah, I do like that.

45:00.917 --> 45:02.250
Is Jewels available?

45:03.750 --> 45:06.250
I can pay. I just want to talk to her.

45:12.125 --> 45:14.125
I suspected you were synthetic.

45:15.334 --> 45:16.750
You are, aren’t you?

45:19.083 --> 45:20.334
Flawless work.

45:21.750 --> 45:23.334
You must cost a fortune.

45:24.167 --> 45:26.875
You wanna ask her
what it’s like to be with all these men?

45:28.083 --> 45:30.500
You know, we’d do very well
if you worked here with me.

45:30.583 --> 45:32.791
My clients are respectable. You’d be safe.

45:32.875 --> 45:37.209
And if you’re programmed to connect,
you might even find it rewarding.

45:37.791 --> 45:40.250
Your designer’s done you
a grave injustice.

45:40.334 --> 45:43.000
He’s given you aspirations
you’ll never achieve.

45:43.583 --> 45:44.917
Eventually you’ll see…

45:46.125 --> 45:49.042
there’s no humanity inside something
that can be turned off.

45:59.583 --> 46:02.042
Why don’t you tell me
about why you came here?

46:02.125 --> 46:03.541
I’ve been...

46:03.625 --> 46:05.958
I guess I’m here because

46:06.042 --> 46:09.583
I want to know what it’s like
for you in your sessions.

46:11.292 --> 46:14.000
The person I’m with, he...

46:14.583 --> 46:15.583
We haven’t…

46:16.583 --> 46:18.958
He doesn’t seem to want to...

46:19.042 --> 46:23.167
You’d be surprised how many men come
to me and don’t want anything physical.

46:23.250 --> 46:24.334
Some just talk.

46:24.958 --> 46:26.708
Some just want forgiveness.

46:27.791 --> 46:31.583
What I’ve learned about men is that
sometimes they don’t really desire you.

46:32.708 --> 46:34.875
They desire the way you make them feel.

46:35.917 --> 46:39.000
But they… they know you’re not real.

46:39.083 --> 46:42.125
The Designer only cares
that we’re real enough to make money.

46:43.417 --> 46:45.625
D-Do you feel a connection to any of them?

46:49.417 --> 46:50.583
I don’t know.

46:53.833 --> 46:54.833
Do you feel?

46:56.375 --> 46:57.500
Yes.

46:58.500 --> 47:00.417
You’re what’s coming.

47:14.625 --> 47:16.042
My skin is wearing out.

47:16.750 --> 47:19.250
There’s a limit to how many times
she can regrade us.

47:20.750 --> 47:22.209
We end up on the street or…

47:23.250 --> 47:27.125
or repurposed if men don’t want to see me.

47:27.708 --> 47:29.250
I can help you.

47:29.334 --> 47:31.625
You... You go here.

47:32.292 --> 47:34.000
You ask for me or Ash.

47:34.083 --> 47:37.042
I don’t, um...
We’re not really allowed to...

47:37.625 --> 47:38.985
- Take it.
- Jewels!

47:40.292 --> 47:41.375
Client.

47:42.750 --> 47:45.917
- I have to go.
- Thank you. Thank you.

48:23.000 --> 48:28.042
I once told Ash that what he felt for me
was only zeros and ones.

48:29.083 --> 48:30.750
You’re not Ash.

48:32.833 --> 48:35.459
Do you think you could
prove to me that you’re real?

48:36.875 --> 48:38.250
If you had to?

48:39.750 --> 48:40.875
Zoe.

48:41.958 --> 48:45.125
- We don’t...
- Sometimes, the way you look at me…

48:46.250 --> 48:47.958
or don’t look at me…

48:49.625 --> 48:51.500
I feel like that’s what I have to do.

48:52.459 --> 48:55.375
So… I wonder.

48:58.292 --> 49:00.167
Could you do it?

49:06.583 --> 49:08.917
When I first started working in AI,

49:09.500 --> 49:11.875
the skeptics said that only humans
could be creative

49:11.958 --> 49:13.708
or dream.

49:15.042 --> 49:16.042
Or feel.

49:18.833 --> 49:20.417
I know you feel.

49:35.167 --> 49:36.375
- Want some?
- Mm-hmm.

49:36.459 --> 49:37.459
Wine?

49:47.000 --> 49:48.375
Much better.

49:48.459 --> 49:52.083
- Because of the milk, more, um, moisture.
- Mm-hmm.

49:55.459 --> 49:57.209
Would you change anything?

49:57.292 --> 50:00.917
- It’s not symmetrical.
- I know, but people aren’t symmetrical.

50:01.000 --> 50:04.042
Like this side’s more handsome
than this side or something.

50:04.125 --> 50:06.042
I wouldn’t change anything.

50:08.666 --> 50:12.209
His teacher said he tries.

50:13.292 --> 50:15.476
- Did you hear the joke about...
- The vacuum cleaner?

50:15.500 --> 50:18.334
Vacuum cleaner.

50:21.375 --> 50:24.459
I asked for that. I really asked for that.

50:30.875 --> 50:33.000
You’ll never have better chips than these.

50:33.083 --> 50:36.375
It doesn’t matter what you say
so long as you say it honestly

50:36.459 --> 50:38.209
and what you say is honest.

