58:00.167 --> 58:03.083
You’ve been hit, okay?
But you’re all right.

58:08.666 --> 58:10.334
- What the hell is that?
- Back off!

58:10.417 --> 58:13.083
You’re okay.
It’s just an emergency protocol, okay?

58:13.167 --> 58:15.042
Your body doesn’t have access
to your organs.

58:17.167 --> 58:20.209
I need you to try to sit up, okay?
Let’s sit up, babe. Come on.

58:20.292 --> 58:22.375
Okay. Okay.

58:22.459 --> 58:24.958
I’m gonna need some help
to get her in my car.

58:25.042 --> 58:27.167
I’m gonna need some help.
Somebody help me.

58:29.750 --> 58:31.167
Hang tight.

58:31.250 --> 58:33.541
- How does it look?
- I don’t know yet. Give me a second.

58:36.625 --> 58:37.917
Here. Thanks.

58:42.209 --> 58:43.209
Okay, scissors.

58:45.375 --> 58:46.417
Okay.

59:03.500 --> 59:06.209
I’m gonna have to perform
a partial shutdown, okay?

59:06.292 --> 59:07.791
It’ll be motion, cognition.

59:07.875 --> 59:10.958
It’ll be like being asleep,
like being in a dream state, okay?

59:11.042 --> 59:12.833
And then I can work on this.

59:13.375 --> 59:16.209
- How long will I be gone for?
- Not very long.

59:18.958 --> 59:19.958
Cole.

59:22.042 --> 59:23.833
What about us?

59:26.500 --> 59:28.292
I need to know.

59:29.708 --> 59:30.791
I, um...

59:32.000 --> 59:33.833
I need to get a few parts.

59:34.625 --> 59:36.042
I’ll be right back. Okay?

59:41.000 --> 59:42.334
It’s okay. It’s okay.

59:45.958 --> 59:47.500
Don’t be too hard on him.

59:49.666 --> 59:51.209
There’s a line, Zoe.

59:52.167 --> 59:55.083
Humans on one side. Machines on the other.

59:57.750 --> 01:00:00.250
And you were on his side of the line
until tonight.

01:00:03.417 --> 01:00:04.459
You and me…

01:00:05.791 --> 01:00:08.417
we can’t find happiness
until we accept who we are.

01:00:12.083 --> 01:00:15.791
You’ll start losing control of your body.
Everything’s gonna start feeling numb.

01:00:15.875 --> 01:00:18.500
- What will happen tomorrow?
- Temperature regulation.

01:00:18.583 --> 01:00:20.875
Tomorrow,
you’ll feel as good as you did today.

01:00:20.958 --> 01:00:22.459
That’s not what I mean.

01:00:23.125 --> 01:00:24.209
Please, Cole.

01:00:24.292 --> 01:00:26.417
I need to know before this happens.

01:00:26.500 --> 01:00:29.417
Don’t look at me like that. It’s still me.

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:31.642
- Everything’s gonna be all right, Zoe.
- It’s still me.

01:00:31.666 --> 01:00:33.625
- Proprioception.
- What about us?

01:00:35.541 --> 01:00:36.666
Please.

01:00:38.083 --> 01:00:40.393
- You’re gonna recover and be strong.
- You need to tell me.

01:00:40.417 --> 01:00:42.083
And whole again.

01:00:42.791 --> 01:00:45.209
I’ll do whatever I can to get you there.

01:00:48.875 --> 01:00:50.375
Zoe.

01:00:51.375 --> 01:00:52.666
I heard you.

01:00:54.459 --> 01:00:57.875
Cole, she’s going into stasis.
Do you want me to do the core systems?

01:00:59.125 --> 01:01:00.209
Cole?

01:01:00.958 --> 01:01:02.292
The core systems?

01:01:03.209 --> 01:01:04.209
Yeah.

01:02:20.334 --> 01:02:21.917
You want to talk about it?

01:02:27.791 --> 01:02:30.417
- Do you know who Eliza was?
- No.

01:02:30.500 --> 01:02:34.250
A really early AI. Software that made you
think you were speaking to a therapist.

01:02:34.334 --> 01:02:38.209
She parroted words back at you.
You’d say, “My mum didn’t love me enough.”

01:02:38.292 --> 01:02:40.185
“Why do you think your mum
didn’t love you enough?”

01:02:40.209 --> 01:02:44.042
You’d say, “My heart hurts.” She would
say, “Why do you think your heart hurts?”

01:02:44.125 --> 01:02:45.459
People loved it.

01:02:46.334 --> 01:02:48.000
The inventor had a secretary.

01:02:48.083 --> 01:02:49.563
She used to ask him to leave the room

01:02:49.625 --> 01:02:53.083
so she could have long, intimate,
personal conversations with her.

01:02:54.958 --> 01:02:58.209
She wanted to be alone
in a room with a few lines of code.

01:02:58.292 --> 01:02:59.750
What are you doing?

01:03:01.292 --> 01:03:02.666
Don’t do this.

01:03:03.917 --> 01:03:06.958
- She’s not that.
- I know that. I guess I know that.

01:03:07.583 --> 01:03:09.250
Let yourself be happy, please.

01:03:09.334 --> 01:03:11.958
I can’t get past it. I tried.
I can’t get past it.

01:03:12.042 --> 01:03:14.167
Just get over it. Okay?

01:03:14.250 --> 01:03:16.083
How? I made her.

01:03:16.167 --> 01:03:18.042
Why don’t you wanna be happy?

01:03:40.042 --> 01:03:41.042
Thank you.

01:03:50.917 --> 01:03:52.167
That’s a Benysol hookup.

01:03:53.459 --> 01:03:55.750
- A what?
- A Benysol hookup.

01:03:55.833 --> 01:04:00.125
Apparently, strangers are doing it now.
It gives them a love high for a few hours.

01:04:01.083 --> 01:04:02.375
Keep seeing it everywhere.

01:04:02.459 --> 01:04:04.666
You mean they didn’t even know each other?

01:04:04.750 --> 01:04:07.125
They probably don’t even like each other.

01:04:07.708 --> 01:04:09.875
But they’re about to fall in love.

01:04:09.958 --> 01:04:11.666
For a few hours, at least.

01:04:16.375 --> 01:04:18.215
First-love doesn’t have to be a memory.

01:04:19.417 --> 01:04:20.791
You can have it now.

01:04:21.375 --> 01:04:22.750
Try Benysol.

01:04:22.833 --> 01:04:26.459
Fall in love for the first time. Again.

01:04:47.917 --> 01:04:49.417
How are you doing?

01:04:51.417 --> 01:04:52.417
I’m good. And you?

01:04:53.209 --> 01:04:54.209
Okay.

01:04:55.167 --> 01:04:58.500
- I heard you’re leaving.
- Well, it’s a sabbatical.

01:04:59.167 --> 01:05:01.791
They still want to use my name
for investments and publicity.

01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:04.500
I just came
to get some stuff from upstairs.

01:05:05.292 --> 01:05:07.250
They’ll be sorry to see you go.

01:05:09.375 --> 01:05:12.459
What I was doing didn’t make much sense
to me anymore after we...

01:05:12.583 --> 01:05:14.083
After we failed.

01:05:15.250 --> 01:05:17.833
Zoe, we never really
got a chance to talk...

01:05:17.917 --> 01:05:20.375
I’ve been surprised how quickly
I’ve been able to move on.

01:05:21.666 --> 01:05:24.334
I’ve been wondering
if that was part of my design.

01:05:27.833 --> 01:05:28.833
No.

01:05:30.250 --> 01:05:32.583
- Don’t say that. No.
- I better get going.

01:05:33.500 --> 01:05:35.250
I have Machine clients waiting.

01:05:59.625 --> 01:06:00.625
It’s crazy.

01:06:04.042 --> 01:06:06.083
Six months after it’s in pharmacies…

01:06:07.791 --> 01:06:09.917
there’s already a gray market for Benysol.

01:06:11.459 --> 01:06:14.209
They’re calling it the Blaze.
I’m seeing it everywhere.

01:06:15.417 --> 01:06:18.917
People like her are hoping we’ll sell
an imperfect batch on the cheap

01:06:19.666 --> 01:06:22.417
or maybe throw some out,
so the blazers can afford to dose.

01:06:23.209 --> 01:06:24.459
It’ll wear off.

01:06:24.541 --> 01:06:26.125
The drug, I mean.

01:06:27.292 --> 01:06:30.000
It’s nothing more than just a Band-Aid,
really.

01:06:32.292 --> 01:06:33.292
Yeah.

01:06:35.250 --> 01:06:37.000
Do you think she’s all right, Ash?

01:06:37.833 --> 01:06:39.791
Sometimes I wonder
why you made me, Cole.

01:06:41.417 --> 01:06:45.000
The mission of the lab is to improve lives
through better relationships.

01:06:46.250 --> 01:06:47.833
That’s what fulfills us.

01:06:51.209 --> 01:06:53.541
- That’s not what I meant.
- I know.

01:06:56.250 --> 01:06:59.292
That’s what I thought
I was doing it for anyway.

01:07:04.666 --> 01:07:06.375
Do you think you would, uh…

01:07:08.791 --> 01:07:10.958
Do you think you might stay on?

01:07:11.791 --> 01:07:12.833
For me?

01:07:15.000 --> 01:07:18.459
- Make me a companion.
- Would that make you happy?

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:31.167
I’m gonna to tell security
to put some locks on the Dumpsters.

01:08:19.042 --> 01:08:20.582
Hey. Are you crushing?

01:08:21.666 --> 01:08:22.957
Sorry?

01:08:23.042 --> 01:08:25.582
I’m just, um, wondering
if you were crushing.

01:08:25.666 --> 01:08:27.125
I’m sorry, I don’t understand.

01:08:27.707 --> 01:08:29.042
I’m sorry.

01:08:29.125 --> 01:08:31.541
I thought you were here for a meet-up.

01:08:31.625 --> 01:08:35.334
- My mistake.
- Uh... No, I’m not sure.

01:08:35.917 --> 01:08:38.750
Is it all right if I sit down
and we just talk for a little while?

01:08:40.625 --> 01:08:42.917
- Michael.
- Zoe.

01:08:43.000 --> 01:08:44.000
Nice to meet you.

01:08:45.334 --> 01:08:46.582
Nice to meet you.

01:10:30.334 --> 01:10:31.334
Do you need some?

01:10:33.209 --> 01:10:34.250
No, I-I’m good.

01:10:34.334 --> 01:10:36.167
I can get you some for 400.

01:10:36.250 --> 01:10:38.750
No, I’m all right. I’m just looking
for someone I know, thanks.

01:10:54.750 --> 01:10:56.042
Just tell me what to do.

01:10:56.125 --> 01:10:57.209
Do you feel it?

01:10:59.292 --> 01:11:01.541
Not yet. Do you?

01:11:02.708 --> 01:11:06.209
A little bit, yeah.
It feels a little less than usual though.

01:11:07.292 --> 01:11:08.791
Here, touch my face.

01:11:11.459 --> 01:11:14.791
- Do you feel it?
- I don’t think I will.

01:11:17.375 --> 01:11:18.875
I’m synthetic.

01:11:21.791 --> 01:11:23.666
That’s probably why
the feeling’s kind of weak.

01:11:40.583 --> 01:11:42.875
Does it matter if I love someone else?

01:11:45.791 --> 01:11:47.625
